review_title: Loose, rattling internals and inconsistent quality
reviews:
Internals in the head are loose. Shakes like a baby rattle. Only reason I opted for a replacement instead of a refund is everyone else raves about this light. I may change my mind once I get the replacement

Update: replacement arrived and this one feels and sounds solid but it's not as bright as the first. The led is not centered like the first one was and its noticable in the beam.

Switch button on both samples is mushy and has bad tactile feel. Host itself is very nice with very good threading and anodizing.

I've opted to just get a refund instead of trying a 3rd time.

reviews: Coming from a guy who's been collecting and using flashlights for a long time now, and it's such a pleasure to to come across brands that are producing good products üëç, and Acebeam is one of those companies, a bit on the expensive side, but you're getting a quality product, I own 3 Acebeams and I've not had one issue since having them , this little palm size light is a blast to use, really good run times , and doesn't get to hot quickly as its only pushing 700+ lumens and with the lens you get a narrow hot spot with little to no spill,as expected with the setup , puts a nice size Hotspot on target. , So keep in mind , if you're looking for something with a hot spot and spill , this is not the one , although it does what its supposed to do really well imho. reviews:
I've become somewhat of a flashlight junkie over the past few months. I'm not quite to doing custom builds, emitter swaps, but I'm still pretty nerdy about this.

I had a chance to play with this in a few country areas, and it's quite impressive, especially given it's size. If you're not familiar with flashlights, this one is a "thrower" that casts a pencil beam long distances. The total lumens may be low, but with great candella, it really can light up quite a ways away. I had 2x ~4000 lumen flooders to compare, and even with the massive lumens, they could only light up a fraction of the distance the E10 was capable of.

review_title: The button ruins an otherwise EXCELLENT light.
reviews:
The amount of light you get in this tiny package is phenomenal, the throw is excellent, the brightness is excellent, and for a paltry little 2000mah battery even the runtime is excellent.

Then there is the button... its mushy at best and in many instances requires upwards of 6 mashes to even respond.

I bought this thinking I could throw this in my pocket and quickly check for animals at night on dog walks but the button is so finicky I cant trust the light to even turn on when I need it, let alone to the brightness I want.

GREAT light, GARBAGE button. Spend your money elsewhere.
